en_56394_0	The bureau of foreign employment says that there is no reason for Sri Lankans employed in South Korea to have any undue fear as a result of the tense atmosphere currently prevalent in North Korea and South Korea.
en_56394_1	Bureau of Foreign Employment Media spokesman, Deputy General Manager Mangala Randeniya said that the Bureau had already prepared a programme that should be implemented if an emergency situation cropped up.
en_56394_2	The spokesman said further that a special discussion of the Bureau of Foreign Employment was also held last afternoon with regard to this.
